Senior Visiting Fellowship Program at the Center for Philosophy of Science
%%%
<p>
The Center for Philosophy of Science at the University of Pittsburgh 
announces a new Senior Visiting Fellowship Program. Applications are 
invited from senior scholars in philosophy of science who wish to spend 
an academic year in the Center. One fellowship will be awarded in the 
coming year.
</p>
<p>
A stipend of $80,000 is offered.
</p>
